name: Letter to Gentleman Jim Stacey
text:
To the esteemed Gentleman Jim Stacey,

Khajit has worked hard to make guild in Gnaar Mok prosperous.

The local Camonna Tong has been eliminated. Their smuggling operation has been taken over. The Hlaalu are bribed, and they allow the guild to operate freely in this town. Khajit could not do any of this without skillful thief who delivers this letter. Khajit recommends skillful thief to the Grandmaster in his struggle against the Camonna Tong and the Fighters' Guild.
Wadarkhu

name: WANTED
text:
WANTED

Reward for the capture of %PCName, the %PCRace with the stated trade of %PCClass, dead or alive. They have committed various crimes against Imperial Law. Report all encounters with this outlaw to the proper authorities. If you see this outlaw in public, give the alarm.

DEAD OR ALIVE!
%PCName

name: Vivec Home Deed
text:
By the Grace of ALMSIVI, Lords and Rulers of All

This document grants all rights of tenancy, residence, bounty, and vocation in the property named Vivec, St. Delyn Waist North-Two, to Delmus Rurvyn.

Seal of Duke Vedam Dren

name: Vivec Home Deed
text:
By the Grace of ALMSIVI, Lords and Rulers of All

This document grants all rights of tenancy, residence, bounty, and vocation in the property named Vivec, St. Delyn Waist North-Two, to Yngling Half-Troll, the Councilor of Great House Hlaalu.

Seal of Duke Vedam Dren
Thieves' Guild: Bal Molagmer, A Room of One's Own

Hreirek the Lean told me that a poor pauper in Vivec City named Delmus Rurvyn was recently evicted from his home by his landlord, Yngling Half-Troll, after losing his job, and not being able to pay the rent. Hreirek has a permanent solution for this problem: I should steal the deed for the property that Rurvyn rented, and return it to Hreirek so that she could make a forged land deed that gives the home to Rurvyn.

I have delivered the original land deed to Hreirek the Lean. She made a forged copy of it, which states that the home belongs to Delmus Rurvyn. I should deliver the new deed to Delmus, who spends most of his time at the St. Delyn Plaza of Vivec.
I have delivered the forged land deed to Delmus Rurvyn.
Hreirek the Lean thanked me for giving the pauper a home.
Tel Fyr: Plundering the Dungeon

The lord of Tel Fyr, Divayth Fyr has told me that I may try to plunder his dungeon, if I feel brave enough. I can find the first key on his table, but after that I'm on my own. I should be careful not to hurt the "inmates" of his Corprusarium and his daughters in the process. If I manage to find his greatest treasure, I should return to him.
I returned to Divayth Fyr with Volendrung, and he restored its enchantments, and acknowledged that I am the first person who could plunder his dungeon.
Thieves' Guild: Free the Prisoners

Wadarkhu told me that we need some new members in Gnaar Mok to make our smuggling operation better. I am to free the Thieves' Guild members who are held prisoner at the Ministry of Truth in Vivec, by giving them a Scroll of Divine Intervention, and telling them to head here. The names of these members are Frizkav Brutya and Vobend Dulfass.
I have freed Frizkav Brutya from prison.
I have freed Vobend Dulfass from prison.

I have reported my success to Wadarkhu about freeing the prisoners. As we are under the protection of the Hlaalu now, the Ordinators should not look for them here, and they can help in our smuggling operation. According to Wadarkhu, they have already arrived, and taken up residence at Nadene Rotheran's shack.
Thieves' Guild: Bal Molagmer, The Loanshark

Hreirek the Lean told me that Helviane Desele owes 200 gold to the loanshark named Manos Othreleth. Manos Othreleth lives at Dren Plantation, while Helviane Desele is the owner of Desele's Earthly Delights in Suran. I should steal the rare book 'Azura and the Box' from Othreleth, and deliver it to Desele. She would be able to sell it, and cover her debt from that.
I have delivered the book 'Azura and the Box' to Helviane Desele.
Hreirek the Lean thanked me for delivering 'Azura and the Box' to Helviane Desele.
Thieves' Guild: Camonna Tong in Gnaar Mok
Wadarkhu asked me to kill the Camonna Tong members in Gnaar Mok, so that we could take over the town. He will take care of any bounty, after I report back to him.
I reported to Wadarkhu that the Camonna Tong members in Gnaar Mok are dead.
Thieves' Guild: Bal Molagmer, Diamonds

Hreirek the Lean asked me to steal at least four diamonds from the mine boss of the Abaelun mine, Mervis. The mine is located to the northeast of Caldera, over the hills. When I have done that, I should deliver the diamonds to Davas Aralas, an exploited diamond miner.
I have delivered the four diamonds to Davas Aralas.
Hreirek the Lean thanked me for delivering the four diamonds to Davas Aralas.
Wadarkhu has asked me to steal a copy of the book titled "The Rear Guard." Anglalos in Gnaar Mok has a copy, either on his person, or in his house.
I have delivered the book titled "The Rear Guard" to Wadarkhu.
Thieves' Guild: The Rear Guard
Thieves' Guild: Taking Over the Smuggling Operation

Wadarkhu wants me to steal ten portions of Moon Sugar and offer it to Valveli Aralas, the shipmaster. Apperently, when the Camonna Tong ruled this town, she used her ship to smuggle goods for them. We want her to do the same for us.
I delivered the Moon Sugar to Valveli Arelas. She will smuggle goods through Gnaar Mok to us, just like she did for the Camonna Tong.
Wadarkhu thanked me for convincing the shipmaster to join us in our smuggling operation.
Thieves' Guild: Deliver a Letter

Wadarkhu told me that he does not have more jobs for me, because he thinks that I'm so skillful that I should work for the Master Thief himself, Gentleman Jim Stacey. He has given a letter of recommendation to me to deliver to him, and as a farewell gift, thought me some tricks about sneaking.
I have delivered the letter to Gentleman Jim Stacey.
Thieves' Guild: Convince Nadene Rotheran

Wadarkhu wants me to convince Nadene Rotheran that similarly to the Camonna Tong, now the Thieves' Guild should be able to use her shack. It should be easy, after I have killed all the Camonna Tong members in this town.
I convinced Nadene Rotheran to use her shack.
Wadarkhu thanked me for convincing Nadene Rotheran about the Thieves' Guild using her shack.
Thieves' Guild: Kill Caryarel
Wadarkhu wants me to kill the freelancer thief in the town named Caryarel.
Wadarkhu thanked me for killing Caryarel.
Thieves' Guild: Collecting Clutter
Wadarkhu asked me to steal 10 goblets for him. Apperently, a client in Mournhold wants it.
I have delivered the 10 goblets to the Thieves' Guild.
Thieves' Guild: Bribing the Hlaalu
Wadarkhu asked me to offer a bribe to Almse Arenim, the Hlaalu who owns Gnaar Mok and the lands around it so that the Thieves' Guild could operate in peace here.
I delivered the money Wadarkhu gave me to Almse Arenim.
Wadarkhu thanked me for bribing Almse Arenim. With the Camonna Tong gone, and the Hlaalu bribed, our work should be easier here.
Thieves' Guild: The Herder's Crook

Wadarkhu wants me to steal Mistress Dratha's staff, which is called "Herder's Crook." The Telvanni Wizard resides in Tel Mora, and she prizes the staff so much that it never leaves her sight. It should be a tough job.
I delivered the "Herder's Crook" to Wadarkhu. He richly rewarded me for this, and for all the work that I have done for him so far.
Congratulations. You are an ambitious and skillful woman who might actually use those treasures, as opposed to him, who would just let them gather dust in order to showcase his male ego.
Ah, here's the skillful thief who managed to plunder my dungeon! We were all impressed by your accomplishment. I hope you enjoy your reward.

Well, you are the first one who actually managed to plunder the dungeon. No, I'm not mad at you, I acknowledge your skill. Give me Volendrung, and I shall restore its enchantments. Congratulations, you are a skillful thief!

If you want to try, you are free to do so. Here is a little hint: The first key is on my table. You can take it, but after that you are on your own. If you actually manage to find my greatest treasure, return to me, and I shall return it to its former glory.

When you live for thousands of years, you need a hobby. Something you love, always sparks your interest. I collect treasures, and invite thieves to steal them. I'm a collector, and a sportsman. I collect enchanted items and ancient artifacts. Have quite a few Dwemer pieces. And, as a sportsman, I love letting thieves try to steal my well-guarded treasures. Only a few rules. One, don't hurt the inmates. Two, don't hurt my daughters. My Warden and guards can look out for themselves.
Congratulations. You are the first one who managed to do this.
I was wrong, and you actually managed to do it. Congratulations! Enjoy your reward.
Well, you are the first good thief we have seen here.
Okay, okay. I acknowledge that you were successful and smart.

Excellent work. It isn't right that a life of any person should be spent in fear for borrowing money once. You have made Vvardenfell a freer place. I have a last job for you. I want you to help out a poor pauper in Vivec City.

Thank you for delivering this book to me. Do you say that you are from the Bal Molagmer? Interesting. I have never heard about them, but I'm certain that this book will be helpful for me to acquire some money.

The owner of Desele's Earthly Delights in Suran, Helviane Desele is indebted to the Cammona Tong loanshark, Manos Othreleth. Manos Othreleth lives at Dren Plantation. The amount Helviane owes to him is 200 gold. As I've learned, Othreleth happens to possess the rare book titled 'Azura and the Box,' and I was thinking: what if we stole that book, gave it to Helviane, so that she could sell it and cover her debt that way, from the loanshark's wealth?

Please excuse poor Ahnassi. She knows you must see her drooping tail and drooping whiskers. But Ahnassi must understand, and save her pride. Ahnassi will pretend she does not care. But to you, Ahnassi can't hide. So sad, so sad, so sad.

Please forgive Ahnassi, if she purrs like a kitten. But Ahnassi is so pleased! You will come visit Ahnassi often then? And tell her things? And ask her things too, for we are now friends, yes? Ahnassi such secrets knows, she almost bursts. Like... Ahnassi MUST tell her new friend! This Hrordis upstairs? Such a secret I know!

What Khajiit can see what she wants, and not take it? Could Ahnassi ask for gift? Don't say 'No' to Ahnassi. Must Ahnassi be the thief? Must she steal this thing, this %PCName she wants? Or will you give yourself as a gift?
result:
; Ahnassi; Agi 50; 
Choice "Give Ahnassi the gift of friendship." 1 "Refuse Ahnassi the gift of friendship." 2

text: Well, %PCRank, %PCName. Ahnassi greets you, with very great pleasure. And Ahnassi hopes you will come to her for training. Ahnassi thinks she would enjoy wrestling with you. Don't you think?
Have you read 'Honor Among Thieves' yet. Don't forget. And please don't forget Ahnassi, either.

No? You aren't in the Guild? That is not right. Ahnassi gives you a present, a copy of this book, 'Honor Among Thieves'. Read this book, as a favor to Ahnassi. No, please, take this gift. Ahnassi thanks you for brightening her day.
How can Ahnassi not see? Must she be blind? She sees you walk, and she likes what she sees. It is her profession, to see such things as the flow of the body, and the grace of the eye, and admire.
I don't know what else the Bal Molagmer should do. But as I know, a sister thief in Dagon Fel, Hreirek the Lean, is quite interested in the Bal Molagmer. Maybe you could visit her?

Now you know as well as I do what the Bal Molagmer should do. I will trust your judgement. By the way, a sister thief in Dagon Fel, Hreirek the Lean, is quite interested in the Bal Molagmer. Maybe you could visit her too?

Now you know as well as I do what the Bal Molagmer should do. I will trust your judgement. By the way, a sister thief in Dagon Fel, Hreirek the Lean, is quite interested in the Bal Molagmer. Maybe you could visit her too?

Oh.... But... it's too much. For Ahnassi? Ahnassi.... It is so lovely. But you must let Ahnassi give you a gift in return. What could possibly be so rare, so fine? Here. Ahnassi gives you these. They are rare and precious. Ahnassi could never use them. But Ahnassi hopes they bring you luck in a hard place.

text: Greetings, fellow thief. I've heard that you belong to the 'Bal Molagmer.' I have a few jobs for you to bring justice to this land. I need someone to help out a poor diamond miner.

Thank you for the letter. Here, take this little gold. Anyone praised by Wadarkhu is worthy to work with me. Also, I'm glad that in Gnaar Mok the guild is prosperous, and everything is all right over there.

Goodbye

text: Are you here to free me, fellow thief? Let me take that scroll, and tell Wadarkhu that I shall travel to Gnaar Mok immediately to participate in your smuggling operation. And thank you.
Are you here to free me, fellow thief? Let me take that scroll, and tell Wadarkhu that I shall travel to Gnaar Mok immediately to participate in your smuggling operation. And thank you.
Fine, we have a deal. I will join your guild, and smuggle goods for you. Give me that moon sugar.
Damn! I never thought that you would be able to bribe them. But what about having a place to store contraband? The Camonna Tong had such a place.
result: Choice "That little girl offered her hut to us too." 3

text: Nonsense! I bet that the Hlaalu now watches your every step, so you cannot hurt me. Why should I smuggle for you, when I can be a freelancer too?
result: Choice "The Hlaalu are in our pockets. Should we tell them that you are a smuggler and have you arrested?" 2

text: So, do you want me to join your guild and smuggle goods for you like I did for the Camonna Tong? And why would I do that?
result: Choice "The Guild is generous to its members. I offer you ten portion of the finest Moon Sugar which you can sell freely. Also, we have taken out the Camonna Tong. We can take out you." 1

text: First the Camonna Tong, now you? Will my suffering never end? Fine, you bully! But if the Camonna Tong comes back to reclaim the hut, I'm not going to do anything about it. You take care of them.
You are the one who killed the Camonna Tong members who threw me out from my house? I cannot thank you enough.
result: Choice "Shut up, and listen. You will offer your hut to the Thieves' Guild now, or you follow your Camonna Tong friends. Understood?" 1

text: I understand. It's an offer that I cannot refuse. For this generous donation, Great House Hlaalu and your guild can exist together in Gnaar Mok.
What do you want?
result: Choice "The Thieves' Guild cares about your people, Almse. It took out the Camonna Tong who terrorized them. Now it offers you this sack of gold to develop the town." 1

text: Rrrrr. When Ahnassi sees smooth moves like this, Ahnassi thinks a dancer. No? A high wall walker? If you aren't in the Thieves Guild, sweet, perhaps you should be.

Oh, well, yes, Ahnassi must tell you, Ahnassi is a thief, yes, but perhaps Ahnassi is a more gentle thief than most. Ahnassi takes things, yes, but not like some. Ahnassi spills no blood. No weapon. No fighting. Ahnassi comes and goes and is not seen. But %PCName is Khajiit, so %PCName understands. A thing is precious, but not protected? That is foolish. And if Ahnassi takes this thing, it is the fool's fault, not Ahnassi. Is that not right?

Oh, well, yes, Ahnassi must tell you, Ahnassi is a thief, yes, but perhaps Ahnassi is a more gentle thief than most. Ahnassi takes things, yes, but not like some. Ahnassi spills no blood. No weapon. No fighting. Ahnassi comes and goes and is not seen. It is not easy to explain to the unclawed. A thing is precious, but not protected? That is foolish. And if Ahnassi takes this thing, it is the fool's fault, not Ahnassi. That is the way of my people.

Ahnassi is a thief, but in mind and spirit Ahnassi is like a monk, a student of the hidden mysteries, of the unseen world. In body, Ahnassi is a student of the ancient martial arts, the 'Rain-of-Sand' style of home. When Ahnassi must defend herself, Ahnassi prefers claw-and-close and wears no armor, because what Ahnassi does not have, Ahnassi cannot lose.

An excellent job. You have done the Bal Molagmer a great service. While the diamond miners are not slaves, if they can barely survive on their wage, are they any better off? Now, I want you to help Helviane Desele next by delivering the book named Azura and the Box to her.

Are those for me? This is a dangerous thing. I don't know how I would smuggle these out from the mine without the guards noticing, but I must try. My poor wife and children are starving. Thank you, kind thief.

Davas Aralas is a poor diamond miner who works in the Abaelun mine, to the northeast of Caldera, over the hills. He, and his fellow miners do all the work, and the owner of the mine, Mervis gets all the profit, while the miners barely have enough to survive. Why don't you steal, let's say, four diamonds from Mervis and give it to Davas Aralas? He deserves it, after all, without him, and his fellow miners, the mine could not operate at all.
Thank you for your work. You are worthy of the Bal Molagmer's legacy, indeed. I don't have any further jobs for you.

So, you say that you're from the Bal Molagmer and you have a document for me? Let me see it. [He reads the land deed.] Well, thank you. But I'm not sure if I'm brave enough to actually move in there... I fear Yngling's wrath.

Do you have the land deed? Good. Give me some time, and I'll make a forgery. [She examines the document and then makes a forged version of it.] Here it is. Now, I'll destroy the original. You should deliver this new version of the document to Delmus Rurvyn. Being without a home, he spends most of his time in the Plaza of the St. Delyn canton nowadays.

A Dunmer in Vivec City, Delmus Rurvyn, has lost his job recently, and was unable to pay the rent to his landlord, Yngling Half-Troll. Of course, Yngling had the Ordinators evict him, and now he doesn't have a place to live. This injustice needs to be remedied. Go to the manor of Yngling Half-Troll in Vivec City, and steal the deed of the home that was rented by Rurvyn, and then return it to me: I am quite good at forging documents. I'll make a forged version which would make the home Delmus' property.

Khajit has no jobs for you. Skillful thief like you should work with Grandmaster of the guild, Gentleman Jim Stacey in Vivec and help him fight against Camonna Tong and Fighters' Guild. Wadarkhu has written letter of recommendation. Deliver it to him. But before we say goodbye, allow Khajit to teach some tricks about his trade for free, as farewell gift.

text: You have done well. Khajit is pleased, and the client will be too. Here, take this generous reward for this job, and also for everything you have done for the guild here, in Gnaar Mok.

Yes, Khajit actually has job for you. Now that Thieves' Guild is prosperous here, clients give us more work. Khajit gives you the most well-paying one: A client wants us to steal the Herder's Crook, which is the prized staff of Mistress Dratha, the Telvanni Wizard of Tel Mora. Dark Elf loves that staff so much that it never leaves her sight. Khajit wishes you good luck on this job.
Khajit thanks you for this deed. Here is shiny gold.

Khajit knows that this is not the way of the Thieves' Guild, but if we want to survive, we must be ruthless. Please kill the High Elf, Caryarel in town. High elf is independent thief, refuses to join Guild. Only if we kill the likes of him and the Camonna Tong can we be the greatest organized crime faction in Morrowind.

You have freed our brother thieves, and they will participate in our smuggling operation, and make the guild stronger here. They are already here, at the shack of Nadene Rotheran. Don't worry, stupid Ordinators won't look for them here, in Gnaar Mok. We are under the protection of the Hlaalu, thanks to Khajit's good thinking.

Guild in Gnaar Mok needs more members to make smuggling more prosperous. Two members of the guild, Frizkav Brutya and Vobend Dulfass are held in Ministry of Truth, Vivec. You will break into the prison and free brother thieves, give them these scrolls and tell them to come here immediately.
Will Dark Elf join our guild and smuggle with us? Great job! The guild in Gnaar Mok will soon be prosperous.

It is time to set up the smuggling operation itself. Luckily, the Camonna Tong was nice and they had left it for us to take. Every week, contraband arrived in the ship of Valveli Arelas, which was stored in the shack of Nadene, until it was sold. With the Camonna Tong gone, the Hlaalu bribed, and the shack taken over, it will be an easy matter to convince Dark Elf to join Thieves' Guild. Steal and then deliver ten portions of Moon Sugar to her as a bribe.
Khajit knew that it will be easy job. Now guild has a place to store contraband. Talk with Khajit again, when you are ready for next job.

With the Camonna Tong gone, and the Hlaalu in our pockets, Wadarkhu wants to make the Gnaar Mok branch of the Guild prosperous. Guild will take over the smuggling operation of the Tong. First thing we need, is a warehouse to store contraband. Go to Nadene Rotheran and convince her to use her shack, like the Tong did. It should be enough, Dark Elf is scared that we killed her friends.
Is the Hlaalu bribed? Great. Now nothing can stop the Thieves' Guild in Gnaar Mok.

Yes, there is still job for you. Almse Arenim is the Hlaalu who owns this town. With the Camonna Tong gone, Dark Elf would surely be willing to allow us operate here. Take this money to Dark Elf, bribe her.

You have done it? Great! Now, there is no competition for us, and we can start to take over this town. Here, take this gold and don't worry, I'll take care of any bounty that you may have on your head. Now, some Camonna Tong members may still show up in this town occasionally: Khajit trusts that you know what Khajit expects from you then.

Leaders of other guildhalls talk about protection against the Tong. Brother and sister thieves make stupid Dwemer machines, hire stupid wizards, and install stupid traps. Wadarkhu says no. Wadarkhu thinks we should destroy the Camonna Tong, take over Gnaar Mok, and protect ourselves from further conflicts as well. Will you do this for me? Kill bad Camonna Tong members and come back. I will take care of any bounty that you may get from this.
Do you have the stupid goblets? Khajit thanks you. Khajit can finally put stupid job behind him.

Yes, Khajit has new job for thief. Fool in Mournhold collects clutter. Fool wants ten goblets like this. Thief should be able to steal them quickly. They are all around Gnaar Mok and other settlements of Morrowind.
You have the book? Great. Here, take this gold. Talk to me again when you are ready for your next job.

text: Yes, Wadarkhu has job for you. Client wants book named "The Rear Guard." The Wood Elf, Anglalos here in Gnaar Mok has that book. Steal it for Wadarkhu. Wood Elf may have it on his person, or in his house. Go, go.
